    h1 Privacy Policy
    div.card.card-body
      p Karasu-OS.com is a fan-made service for the game Obey Me! Shall We Date developed by NTT Solmare Corp. The service is completely free to use and is a completely separate entity from the game itself. To create an account for the service on Karasu-OS.com, a username and password is required. You have the choice to link a verified email for password recovery, which is completely optional. Karasu-OS.com does not associate this data with you or your identities, nor will we distribute or sell information to third-party organizations.
      h5 Cookies
      p Karasu-OS.com uses cookies to keep track of your preferences and login sessions on the website. You can disable the use of cookies by adjusting the settings on your browser (see your browser Help for how to do this). Be aware that disabling cookies will result in disabling certain functionalities and features of the website. Therefore it is recommended that you leave the cookies setting on.
      h5 Links to External Sites
      p Karasu-OS.com contains links to other websites. We provide the links for your convenience, but we do not review, control, or monitor the privacy practices of websites operated by others.
      h5 Privacy Policy Revisions
      p This Privacy Policy was last revised on 06 November 2024. We may change this Privacy Policy at any time and for any reason. If we make a significant change to our policies, we will post a notice after the change is made.
